<head>
<title>Fellowships, Grants and Funding Opportunities</title>
</head>
<body>
<a name=#A> </a>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<h2>Fellowships, Grants and Funding Opportunities</h2>
<ul>
<li><a 
href="gopher://gopher.sscnet.ucla.edu:70/00/Geography/Climatology/ftp.gradgide">
AAG-CSG Guide to Graduate Programs in Climatology</a><br>
A guide to Geography Department graduate degree programs in climatology prepared 
by the Climate Specialty Group of the Association of American Geographers.<p>
<li><a href="http://cos.gdb.org/">Community of Science  Web Server</a><br>
Links to Federally-funded research and a searchable database with multiple "picklists" 
or fields(such as funding type, sponsors, and programs) that narrows searches to 
identify very specific results.   This international database includes federal agencies, 
state/provincial and commercial organizations, non-profit foundations and professional 
associations. <p>
<li><a href="http://atm.geo.nsf.gov/AMS/amsedu/97global.html">Graduate Student Scholarships: Symposium on Global Change Studies</a><br>
Scholarships are supported by the American Meteorological Society and the
National Science Foundation.<p>   
<li><a href="http://www.hq.nasa.gov/office/mtpe/mtpe_mail.html">Mission to Planet Earth Update</a><br>
For information about current and past Mission to Planet Earth NASA Research
Announcements (NRAs solicit proposals from the scientific community to perform
 research) and fellowships. Join this list to receive announcements by email.<p>
<li><a href="http://solstice.crest.org/renewables/grad/">Directory of 
Energy-Related Graduate Programs in U.S. Universities</a><br>
Hundreds of listings for graduate-level energy programs in the U.S.  Published in 1992 
by the Energy Foundation.<p>
<li><a href="http://web.fie.com/htdoc/fed/all/any/any/menu/any/index.htm">FEDIX(Federal Information Exchange)</a><br>
Free on-line information retrieval service of federal opportunities for the education and 
research communities that includes a searchable database of 1,300+ federally-sponsored 
research, education and minority programs with complete descriptions and full contact 
information. Includes, Opportunity Alert, an e-mail alert service that delivers announcements of new funding opportunities that match your interest.<p> 
<li><a href="http://www.cs.yale.edu/HTML/YALE/CS/HyPlans/tap/fellowships.html">Fellowship/Grant/Award Information</a><br>
A variety of helpful resources that includes financial aid information and the Fulbright Scholars Program and the Fulbright Teacher Exchange Program.<p>
<li><a href="http://www.utulsa.edu/GrantsWeb.html">GrantsWeb</a><br>
Offers links to Federal and non-Federal granting programs, other databases, and
pointers on successful grantwriting.<p>
<li><a href="http://www.vsp.ucar.edu/97.noaa.poster.html">1997 NOAA 
Postdoctoral Program in Climate and Global Change</a><br>
The objective of this program is to help create the next generation of climate researchers.  
Managed by the University Corporation for  Atmospheric Research (UCAR) for NOAA, 
the program pairs recent postdoctorates with research scientists at U.S. institutions.<p>
<li><a href="http://www.orau.gov/seed/seedfact.htm">Oak Ridge Institute for Science and Education (SEED)
The Science/Engineering Education Division</a><br>
Programs for faculty members; postgraduates; graduate and undergraduate 
students; and teachers and students in grades K-12.<p>
</ul><p>
<p align=center>
