<title>Volcanic Eruptions</title>
<body>

<img align=left alt=Mount St. Helens src=gifs/pg66.gif>

Volcanic eruptions can emit large quantities of gases and aerosols to 
the atmosphere.  Although emissions from the Mt. Saint Helens 
eruption (shown here) did not reach the stratosphere, they did cause 
air quality problems downwind and large quantities of ash were 
deposited over a wide region.
</body>

