<title>Ice Core Record</title>
<body>
<p align=center><img align=left alt=Ice Core Record src=gifs/pg65v.gif>

<p>(Left) Calcium record over 100,000 years measures atmospheric dust and 
documents frequent, abrupt changes in climate, especially during the glacial 
period.<p>

(Right) The period known as the Younger Dryas (approximately 11.5 to 13 thousand years ago represents a return to near glacial conditions, being about 7 &#176 Ccooler and about half as much ice accumulation (precipitation) as during the 
subsequent period.
</body>

