<title>Our Changing Planet - Ocean Modeling</title>
<body>

<img align=left alt=Model Visualizations src=gifs/pg68o.gif>

<h2>Global ocean model simulation</h2>

Sea surface temperatures produced by the most detailed global ocean model to 
date.  Warm tempertures in the tropical oceans are shown in red, and colder 
temperatures in purple.  This model can simulate the great detail of the 
Gulf Stream, the Kuroshio Current near Japan, and the Antarctic Circumpolar
Current, and provides important information on the structure of the ocean.

</body>
</DOC>
