<html><head><title>Welcome to EarthPulse NEWS</title></head>
<body>
Welcome to EarthPulse NEWS.  Our purpose is to provide K-12 
teachers and students, and anyone else interested in how the Earth is 
changing, with an accessible summary of some of the latest 
developments in global change, with an emphasis on climate and its 
effects on the biosphere.  Background and context are provided as 
needed, and some suggestions for integrating these topics into 
classroom curricula are offered.  Terms which may be unfamiliar to 
some readers are underlined; clicking on these terms takes the user 
to their definitions.  As the study of many of these topics is highly 
interdisciplinary and relatively new, we will try to direct you to 
resources for more information.<p>

The climate-related topics featured in EarthPulse NEWS touch nearly 
every aspect of our lives, from the energy we use to stay warm or 
cool in our homes, schools and workplaces, to how well our food 
grows, to the range of songbirds we hope will visit our windowsills.  
Your questions, correspondence, ideas for additional activities, and 
results of experiments are most welcome and we hope will become a 
regular feature.  Please e-mail correspondence to <a href="mailto:shassol@agci.org">shassol@agci.org</a><p>
</body>
</html>

