<H2><A NAME="cspstaff"><B>U.S. Country Studies Management
Team</A><B></H2>
<P>
<H4><P>
The Country Studies Management Team (CSMT) provides oversight for
U.S. CSP projects,
materials, and workshops. If you have questions about a specific
country or sector of the U.S. CSP,
please contact the appropriate CSMT coordinator. <I>E-mail</I>,
fax
numbers, and regular
mailing addresses are listed below.<BR>
<P>The mailing address and fax numbers for all members of the
CSMT:  <BR>
<I>**Please note new address and fax numbers for the
USCSP**</I><BR>
<P>
<B>U.S. Country Studies Program<BR>
Forrestal Building, PO-6, Room GP-196<BR>
1000 Independence Avenue, SW<BR>
Washington, DC  20585<BR>
USA<BR>
<P>
<I>fax</I>: 202-586-3485/3486</B><BR>
<P>
<B>E-mail:</B> <ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:csmt@igc.apc.org"><I>
csmt@igc.apc.org</I></A></ADDRESS>
<P>
<P><UL>
<LI><A HREF="#region"><I>Regional Coordinators</I></A>
<UL><LI>Africa
<LI>Asia
<LI>Central & Eastern Europe
<LI>Former Soviet Union
<LI>Island Nations
<LI>Latin America
<LI>Middle East</UL>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="#sector"><I>Sector Study Coordinators</I></A>
<UL><LI>Emissions Inventory
<LI>Vulnerability and Adaptation Assessment
<LI>Mitigation Assessment
<LI>Technology Assessment
<LI>Support for National Action Plans (SNAP)</UL>
<P>
<P>
</H4>
