<html><head><title>U.S. Country Studies - Beijing Workshop</title>
</head>
<body>
<H1><A NAME="China"><CENTER>International Workshop on<BR>
Greenhouse Gas Mitigation
Technologies and Measures</A></H1>
<P>
<H2><I><B>Beijing, The People's Republic of China</B><BR>
November 12-15, 1996</I></CENTER></H2>
<P>
<HR>
<H4>The International Workshop on Greenhouse Gas Mitigation
Technologies and Measures
is co-sponsored by the U.S. Country Studies Program (USCSP),
Deutsche Gesellschaft fuer
Technische Zusammenarbeit (GTZ) mbH, the People's Republic of
China (PRC) State Science
& Technology Commission (SSTC) and other co-sponsors.  The
workshop will provide an
international forum for the exchange of information among
representatives of countries
conducting studies on greenhouse gas mitigation technologies and
measures, and other
international experts.  Participants will share and discuss the
results of their work on
mitigation measures and technology assessment and will have the
opportunity to discuss the
preparation and implementation of mitigation action plans.  The
technical workshop
proceedings will be published in both Chinese and English.</H4>
<P>
<P><H5>
<H4><I><B>Objectives</B></I></H4>
<UL><LI>Promote exchange of information on climate change
mitigation/technologies and
measures.
<LI>Discuss country specific approaches to developing mitigation
measures and technology
programs and projects.
<LI>Identify and discuss issues of particular importance to
developing and transition
countries, such as the barriers to the diffusion of greenhouse
gas emission mitigation
technologies 
<LI>Facilitate networking and cooperation among participants and
institutions involved in
development of climate change mitigation programs.</UL>
<P>
<P>
<H4><I><B>Major Topics</B></I></H4>
<UL><LI>GHG mitigation assessment findings and the factors and
criteria that should be
considered in GHG mitigation measures.
<LI>The barriers that hinder GHG technology transfer and
implementation, and discussion of
the role of international organizations and financial
organizations.
<LI>The role of the study of GHG technology assessment in
formulating national mitigation
plans and implementation strategies.
<LI>Key issues faced by countries in preparing mitigation action
plans and mitigation
elements of national communications.</UL>
<P>
<P>
<H4><B><I>Participants</B></I></H4>
<UL><LI>Representatives from developing and transition countries
that are evaluating
mitigation technologies and measures and preparing mitigation
action plans.
<LI>Regional and international organizations.
<LI>Climate change, technology science, and policy experts from
around the world.
<LI>Representatives from donor countries and organizations.</UL>
<P>
<P>
<H4><I><B>Translation</B></I><BR></H4>
The workshop will be conducted in English and Chinese.  There
will be simultaneous
interpretation into both Chinese and English.  The papers will
all be written in English.
<P>
<P>
<H4><B><I>Publications</I><B><BR></H4>
<H5>All participants are encouraged to present papers on
assessment
of mitigation technolgies and 
measures and development of mitigation plans.  Please send an
abstract of 400 words or less
to Ms. Liu Bin at the Chinese Country Studies Office address
(below) by April 30th, 1996. 
A proceedings will be published after the workshop.  All papers
are subject to peer review
before being considered for publication.  Hard copies and an
electronic version on diskettes
must be brought to the workshop for inclusion in the
publication.</H5>
<P>
<P>
<H4><I><B>Contacts</B></I><BR></H4>
<H5>For further information please contact the workshop
co-organizers listed below:</H5>
<P>
<H5><I><B>Ron Benioff</B><BR>
U.S. Country Studies Program<BR>
1000 Independence Ave., S.W.<BR>
Mail Stop: PO-63<BR>
Washington, D.C.  20585   USA<BR>
<P>
<I>Tele</I>:  202-426-0011<BR>
<I>Fax</I>: 202-426-1540<BR>
<I>E-mail: <ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:csmt@igc.apc.org">
csmt@igc.apc.org</I></A></ADDRESS>
<P>
<B>Professor Wu Zongxin</B><BR>
China Country Study Office (CCSO)<BR>
Energy Science Bldg, Tsinghua University<BR>
Beijing 100084, PRC<BR>
<P>
<I>Tele</I>: 8610-259-4828<BR>
<I>Fax</I>: 8610-256-4177<BR>
<I>E-mail: <ADDRESS><A
HREF="mailto:THINET@beep2.ihep.ac.cn>THINET@beep2.ihep.ac.cn
</ADDRESS></I></A></H5></I><BR>
