<title>Fig 7 - Model Forum Report</title>
<body>

<img alt=sea level projections align=bottom src=gifs/fig7thumb.gif>

<p>
<strong>Figure 7.</strong>  Model projections of the increase (in cm) 
in global-mean sea level corresponding to IPCC concentration 
scenario IS95a.  Projections are for medium ice-melt parameters and 
different climate sensitivities to a doubling of carbon dioxide 
concentration:  (a) 1.5 &#176 , (b) 2.5 &#176 , and (c) 4.5 &#176 
C. [Source:  T. Wigley, UCAR].  Note that the rise will continue long 
into the future as the oceans adjust to warming temperatures.
