known as the 
"horse latitudes."  In the northern hemisphere, they correspond roughly with 
the deserts of northern Mexico, the Sahara in northern Africa, the Arabian 
Desert and the great Indian Desert, in the southern hemisphere, with the 
Atacama Desert of Chile, Peru and Bolivia, the Kalahari Desert of southern 
Africa, and the deserts of Australia.

