<title>Fig 12 - Model Forum Report</title>
<body>

<img alt=Oxygen isotope records align=bottom src=gifs/fig12thumb.gif>

<p>
<strong>Figure 12.</strong>  Oxygen isotope records recorded in the 
layers of snow of the Greenland ice sheet, shown here as the 
departure of the oxygen-18 isotope [d<sup>18</sup>O in parts per 
thousand (o/oo)] versus time (in thousands of years before present).  
The right-hand scale shows deviations from mean Holocene 
temperatures assuming that the d<sup>18</sup>O deviation from the 
mean Holocene d<sup>18</sup>O of 34.8 o/oo is caused by local 
temperature changes with a d<sup>18</sup>O-temperature 
coefficient of 0.63 o/oo per &#176 C [Source:  P. Grootes and M. 
Stuiver, University of Washington; and Greenland Ice Sheet Project 2 
(GISP2), University of New Hampshire].
</body>
